name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: fs.s3a.multipart.purge.age
description:
Minimum age in seconds of multipart uploads to purge
    on startup if "fs.s3a.multipart.purge" is true

name: io.seqfile.compress.blocksize
description:
The minimum block size for compression in block compressed
          SequenceFiles.

name: mapreduce.job.speculative.retry-after-speculate
description:
The waiting time(ms) to do next round of speculation
  if there are tasks speculated in this round.

name: dfs.storage.policy.satisfier.queue.limit
description:
Storage policy satisfier queue size. This queue contains the currently
    scheduled file's inode ID for statisfy the policy.
    Default value is 1000.

name: dfs.datanode.bp-ready.timeout
description:
The maximum wait time for datanode to be ready before failing the
    received request. Setting this to 0 fails requests right away if the
    datanode is not yet registered with the namenode. This wait time
    reduces initial request failures after datanode restart.
    Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive), as described
    in dfs.heartbeat.interval.If no time unit is specified then seconds
    is assumed.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.suspectnode.interval.ms
description: Interval time in milliseconds for probing suspect node behavior.

name: dfs.client.failover.connection.retries.on.timeouts
description:
Expert only. The number of retry attempts a failover IPC client
    will make on socket timeout when establishing a server connection.
